      "raw_text": "SEATTLE, Jan. 4.-Angered be-\ncause the Yukon-Alaska fair direc-\ntorate would not bind itself to en-\nplny only union labor, the Building\nTrades council last night met and\ncalled upon union men everywhere\ntofboycott the fair and work in OPP\nposition to 1t.\n\n\nPresident Chilberg, Of the expo\nsition, said after action was taken:\n\n\n1.-THE money for the exposition\ncame from all classes and the work\nwill be distributed the same way.\nWe will play no favorites.\n\n\nThe open shop agitation in Seat\ntie may result in a general walkout\nIn the building trades. Several con-\ntractors have announced their in\ntention to employ both union and\nnonunion men If they desire. The\ncontractor of a new $4,000 church\nput on a force of nonunion men\nyesterday."
